Trying to tackle a to-do list or binge-watching my favorite show - we've all been there. But before I reach for the coffee or remote control, I ask myself: what's the right choice? The classic "WWJD" (what would Jesus do?) dilemma. Would He grab a venti iced coffee and power through or take a load off on the couch? 

Considering His teachings on self-care and compassion, maybe He'd opt for a more balanced approach. A short walk, some meditation, a healthy snack - not exactly the recipe for an epic Netflix binge. Still, we can't help but wonder: would He give in to our cravings or encourage us to be more mindful? Perhaps the answer lies in finding a balance between productivity and rest. 

After all, Jesus didn't say, "Crash on your sofa and binge-watch your worries away." He said, 'Come unto me, weary and heavy-laden,' implying we should come to Him with our burdens, not our snack bowls. So, next time you're torn between a productive day and a relaxing evening, ask yourself: which path aligns with Jesus' teachings?
